defs.name: Separator
defs.docs:
Represents a separator. The symbol is the character which will be used for separate the string
 and the keep if it'll be considered as a token or not.

defs.name: Filter
defs.docs:
A filter contains a list of tuples with the characters that will be used as separators, and a
 boolean indicatinf whether or not they'll be a token

defs.name: contains
defs.docs:
Returns Some(bool) if the set contains the char. The bool represents
 if the separator has to be keeped as a token or not.

defs.name: add_separator
defs.docs:
Add a separator to the separators set. Since it is a set,
 separators cannot be repeated

defs.name: new_default
defs.docs:
Initializes a Tokenizer with the default filter which only separates the string
 by white spaces and doesn't cosider them as tokens. It has the same functionality
 as the std function split_whitespace()

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Initializes a tokenizer with a filter specified by the user.

defs.name: tokenize
defs.docs:
Use the filter to generate a Vec of Strings in which every element is a "token".
 If the separator is set to true, the separator will also be added as a token.

defs.name: create_token
defs.value: fn (&self, chars: &Vec<char>, start: usize, end: usize) -> Option<String>
defs.docs:
Splits a char Vec at the specified points, start and end, then collects that array into
 a String and finally if that string is empty returns None, otherwise returns
 the string.
